From c1c239d5352aebc5516ecf3759354aac4cfca3f6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "LU, Xinbo" <luxinbo4@huawei.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Apr 2026 14:37:55 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] tr181-firewall: validate rule IP and mask fields separately
 [PPW-1462]

Problem: Current implementation treats SourceMask and DestMask as full IP
addresses when applying firewall rules.

According to TR-181:
- SourceIP/DestIP must contain only host IP addresses
- SourceMask/DestMask must be in IP prefix (CIDR) format

The IP portion of the mask field should be ignored, and only the
prefix length used for matching.

Solution: Add dedicated validators for rule IP addresses and rule mask
values. Update rule event handling to apply the configured mask to the
current IP and push the resulting network/prefix to the firewall backend.

Fixes: PPW-1462
Reference: https://prplfoundation.atlassian.net/browse/PPW-1462
Signed-off-by: LU, Xinbo <luxinbo4@huawei.com>
